        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-700">The average professional loses <strong>2.1 hours daily</strong> to distractions and inefficient workflows. By implementing these 15 hacks, you can reclaim that time and boost your output dramatically.</p>
    </div>

    <h2>1. Time Blocking: Schedule Like a CEO</h2>
    <p><strong>Time blocking</strong> is the practice of dividing your day into dedicated blocks for specific tasks. Instead of reacting to whatever comes your way, you proactively control your schedule.</p>

    <div class="bg-blue-50 p-4 rounded-lg my-4">
        <p class="font-semibold mb-2"><i class="fas fa-check-circle text-green-600 mr-2"></i>How to Implement:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Review your tasks the night before</li>
            <li>Assign specific time blocks (e.g., 9-11 AM: Deep work)</li>
            <li>Include buffer time between blocks</li>
            <li>Color-code your calendar for visual clarity</li>
            <li>Protect your blocksâ€”treat them as unmissable meetings</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <!-- Tool Link -->
    <div class="bg-gradient-to-r from-purple-50 to-blue-50 border-l-4 border-purple-500 p-4 my-4 rounded">
