    <h2>2. The Pomodoro Technique</h2>
    <p>The <strong>Pomodoro Technique</strong> involves working in focused <strong>25-minute intervals</strong> (called "pomodoros") followed by 5-minute breaks.</p>

    <div class="bg-red-50 p-4 rounded-lg my-4">
        <p class="font-semibold mb-2"><i class="fas fa-clock text-red-600 mr-2"></i>The Process:</p>
        <ol>
            <li>Set a timer for 25 minutes - Focus on one task only</li>
            <li>Work without distractions until the timer rings</li>
            <li>Take a 5-minute break</li>
            <li>After 4 pomodoros, take a longer 15-30 minute break</li>
        </ol>
    </div>

    <!-- Tool Link -->
    <div class="bg-gradient-to-r from-red-50 to-orange-50 border-l-4 border-red-500 p-4 my-4 rounded">
